, harmonic, arrangement, and narrative fields<br/>- `/tmp/current_score_tree.json` or configured state path is written when a live piece starts<br/>- tests verify restart-safe load of active and queued score trees |\\n+my-claw/sdp/prd-music-production-course.md:40:- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/score_tree.py`\\n+my-claw/sdp/prd-music-production-course.md:41:- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/recursive_composer.py`\\n+my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:23:**In scope:** a new rendering stage between composition and synthesis; an Event/PerformanceIntent/SectionEnvelope data model with rule-stack provenance; a 12-rule render stack (R1–R12); a seeded-RNG architecture with per-stage sub-seeds; a replay harness; a rule-ablation debugger; a metrics-CI gate with anti-pattern detection; a performance-worm diagnostic; a bounded sensor-to-intent aggregation matrix.\\n+my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:41:**Phase 4 — Sensor aggregation + narrative coupling (CCH-030..CCH-033).** R12 Sensor-to-intent matrix (smoothed IIR, hysteresis, aggregate intentions — never one-to-one). Bounded reactive delta track. Narrative engine → SectionEnvelope coupling. End-of-phase: installation responds legibly to audience presence without gimmicky mappings.\\n+my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:55:  - `render/events.py` — Event, PerformanceIntent, SectionEnvelope, IntentTag, Role dataclasses\\n+my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:64:- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/score_tree.py` — score-tree nodes carry PerformanceIntent / SectionEnvelope metadata\\n+my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:65:- **Extended** `my-claw/tools/senseweave/recursive_composer.py` — emits score-tree with new metadata; composition seed threaded through\\n+my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:76:| CCH-002 | Implement PerformanceIntent per-phrase metadata with arc shape, deviation bounds, tension target, restraint, and call/response role. | MUST | T1 | - `render/events.py` defines PerformanceIntent(phrase_id, arc_shape, arc_peak_position, tempo_deviation_pct, dynamic_range_db, articulation_mean, breath_after_ms, tension_target, restraint, call_response_role)<br/>- arc_shape is one of parabolic/cosine/bezier/flat/inverted<br/>- conservative defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, dynamic_range_db=9, arc_peak_position=0.6, breath_after_ms=250, restraint=0.0<br/>- tests verify defaults match research-calibrated KTH k=1 values and reject out-of-range inputs |\\n+my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:77:| CCH-003 | Implement SectionEnvelope with breakpoint functions over tempo_base, density_target, dynamic_plane, brightness, tension_trajectory. | MUST | T1 | - `render/events.py` defines SectionEnvelope with breakpoint-function interpolation (linear default, optional spline)<br/>- envelope samples at arbitrary normalized position 0..1 within section<br/>- phrase-arc rules compose multiplicatively with section-envelope samples<br/>- tests verify interpolation, composition with phrase arcs, and parameter bounds |\\n+my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:78:| CCH-004 | Define IntentTag enum (build/settle/question/answer/withhold/punctuate) and require every phrase to carry one. | MUST | T1 | - IntentTag enum exists in `render/events.py` with exactly six values<br/>- composition gate rejects phrases missing intent_tag on long pieces<br/>- micro pieces may use punctuate as the default<br/>- tests verify enum completeness and gate rejection path |\\n+my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:81:| CCH-007 | Refactor composition stage to emit score-tree with PerformanceIntent + SectionEnvelope + IntentTag metadata, deterministic from composition seed. | MUST | T1 | - `recursive_composer.py` and `score_tree.py` extended to attach PerformanceIntent to every phrase node and SectionEnvelope to every section node<br/>- composer accepts an explicit composition_seed argument and produces byte-identical score trees for the same seed + brief<br/>- existing pieces still compose successfully; gate passes on unchanged repertoire<br/>- tests verify determinism (two runs same seed → equal score-tree hash) and metadata presence |\\n+my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:83:| CCH-009 | Build a deterministic replay harness that reproduces any past performance from (score, composition_seed, interpretation_seed, delta_track). | MUST | T1 | - `render/replay.py` exposes replay(score, seeds, delta_track) returning PerformedPart byte-identical to original<br/>- delta_track is persisted as JSON per run alongside audio output<br/>- tests verify: re-render with same inputs produces identical Event sequence (hash match) including all timing, velocity, and articulation values |\\n+my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:85:| CCH-011 | Build the RenderPass framework: ordered rule stack with stable order, per-rule enable flags, per-rule quantity k, and role-filter gating. | MUST | T1 | - `render/pass_.py` defines RenderPass(rules, enabled_flags, quantities) with apply(score_tree, seeds) → PerformedPart<br/>- rule order is fixed and documented: R1→R2→R3→R4→R5→R6→R7→R8→R9→R10→R11→R12<br/>- per-rule k defaults to 1.0; authoring surface exposes overrides per-piece and per-intent-tag<br/>- tests verify stable order, k=0 equals rule-disabled, k=1 equals calibrated default |\\n+my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:87:| CCH-013 | Implement R2 Phrase Arch (Todd/KTH): parabolic tempo + loudness arch over each phrase, modulated by section envelope. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/phrase_arch.py` computes tempo_mult(x) = 1 + k·(-4·(x-peak)² + 1)·tempo_deviation_pct/100 and matching amp_mult for normalized phrase position x<br/>- defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, peak=0.6, k=1.0<br/>- arc_shape parameter supports parabolic, cosine, asymmetric-Bezier, flat, inverted variants<br/>- composes multiplicatively with SectionEnvelope.tempo_base at each event<br/>- tests verify arc shape, peak position, and multiplicative composition |\\n+my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:99:| CCH-025 | Implement R11 Call-Response Gating: follower phrase intent complements leader's realized performance. | MUST | T1 | - `render/rules/call_response.py` reads leader voice's PerformedPart and transforms follower's PerformanceIntent before follower render<br/>- leader build → follower descends from apex; leader pause → follower fills<br/>- respects existing role metadata (leader/follower/solo/tacet) from production-course PRD<br/>- tests verify complementarity on 2-voice fixture |\\n+my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:100:| CCH-026 | Compose SectionEnvelope with phrase arcs multiplicatively so section-level tempo elasticity modulates phrase-level shaping. | MUST | T1 | - at each event, final_tempo_mult = section_envelope.tempo_base(t) × phrase_arch.tempo_mult(x) × (1 + sensor_tempo_scale)<br/>- clamp composed result to ±15% bounds<br/>- tests verify multiplicative composition and clamp behavior |\\n+my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:102:| CCH-028 | Add arc-shape variety so not every phrase uses a symmetric parabola: per-phrase random selection from parabolic/cosine/asymmetric-Bezier/flat/inverted with peak-position variance. | MUST | T1 | - arc_shape selected from PerformanceIntent or, if unspecified, sampled from authored distribution weighted by intent_tag<br/>- for intent_tag=withhold, occasional flat arc (tempo_deviation_pct=0) is expressive<br/>- tests verify shape distribution over many phrases and flat-arc presence for withhold intent |\\n+my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:103:| CCH-029 | Implement restraint parameter enforced as global dampener across rules. | MUST | T1 | - PerformanceIntent.restraint ∈ [0, 1] scales: tempo_deviation_pct (× (1-restraint)), dynamic_range_db (× (1-restraint·0.7)), silence-budget thresholds (× (1 + restraint))<br/>- R2, R10 read restraint at runtime<br/>- tests verify restraint=0 is neutral and restraint=1 produces near-flat phrases with extended silence |\\n+my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:106:| CCH-032 | Couple narrative engine to SectionEnvelope selection so dramatic arcs drive section choice. | SHOULD | T2 | - narrative beat → SectionEnvelope mapping exposed via existing narrative engine interface<br/>- section choice respects tension_trajectory + tone_vector from narrative tone controller<br/>- tests use fixture beats and verify expected section envelopes selected |\\n+my-claw/sdp/prd-cypherclaw-humanization.md:113:| CCH-039 | Embed rule-stack provenance in exported audio metadata (e.g., WAV iXML chunk or sidecar JSON) for listener-review workflow. | MUST | T1 | - each rendered audio file gets a `.render.json` sidecar with Event list, rule_stack per event, PerformanceIntent per phrase, SectionEnvelope per section, seeds, delta_track path<br/>- format documented in `my-claw/docs/render-audio-sidecar.md`<br/>- tests verify sidecar presence, schema, and ability to replay from sidecar alone |\\n+sdp/logs/Lead_T-018_20260416T181925Zd_1776390913.log:1749:tests/test_repertoire_memory_score_tree.py .                             [ 77%]\\n+sdp/logs/Lead_T-018_20260416T181925Zd_1776390913.log:1766:tests/test_score_tree.py .                                               [ 82%]\\n+sdp/logs/Lead_T-018_20260416T181925Zd_1776390913.log:1767:tests/test_score_tree_composer.py ....................                   [ 83%]\\n+sdp/logs/Lead_T-018_20260416T181925Zd_1776390913.log:1768:tests/test_score_tree_pipeline.py .                                      [ 83%]\\n+sdp/logs/Lead_T-028_20260416T181925Z_1776400429.log:11:- PerformanceIntent.restraint ∈ [0, 1] scales: tempo_deviation_pct (× (1-restraint)), dynamic_range_db (× (1-restraint·0.7)), silence-budget thresholds (× (1 + restraint))<br/>- R2, R10 read restraint at runtime<br/>- tests verify restraint=0 is neutral and restraint=1 produces near-flat phrases with extended silence\\n+sdp/logs/Lead_T-028_20260416T181925Z_1776400429.log:41:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"message\\\",\\\"timestamp\\\"