| - `render/rules/call_response.py` reads leader voice's PerformedPart and transforms follower's PerformanceIntent before follower render<br/>- leader build → follower descends from apex; leader pause → follower fills<br/>- respects existing role metadata (leader/follower/solo/tacet) from production-course PRD<br/>- tests verify complementarity on 2-voice fixture |\\n+sdp/prd-snapshot.md:106:| CCH-026 | Compose SectionEnvelope with phrase arcs multiplicatively so section-level tempo elasticity modulates phrase-level shaping. | MUST | T1 | - at each event, final_tempo_mult = section_envelope.tempo_base(t) × phrase_arch.tempo_mult(x) × (1 + sensor_tempo_scale)<br/>- clamp composed result to ±15% bounds<br/>- tests verify multiplicative composition and clamp behavior |\\n+sdp/prd-snapshot.md:108:| CCH-028 | Add arc-shape variety so not every phrase uses a symmetric parabola: per-phrase random selection from parabolic/cosine/asymmetric-Bezier/flat/inverted with peak-position variance. | MUST | T1 | - arc_shape selected from PerformanceIntent or, if unspecified, sampled from authored distribution weighted by intent_tag<br/>- for intent_tag=withhold, occasional flat arc (tempo_deviation_pct=0) is expressive<br/>- tests verify shape distribution over many phrases and flat-arc presence for withhold intent |\\n+sdp/prd-snapshot.md:109:| CCH-029 | Implement restraint parameter enforced as global dampener across rules. | MUST | T1 | - PerformanceIntent.restraint ∈ [0, 1] scales: tempo_deviation_pct (× (1-restraint)), dynamic_range_db (× (1-restraint·0.7)), silence-budget thresholds (× (1 + restraint))<br/>- R2, R10 read restraint at runtime<br/>- tests verify restraint=0 is neutral and restraint=1 produces near-flat phrases with extended silence |\\n+sdp/prd-snapshot.md:112:| CCH-032 | Couple narrative engine to SectionEnvelope selection so dramatic arcs drive section choice. | SHOULD | T2 | - narrative beat → SectionEnvelope mapping exposed via existing narrative engine interface<br/>- section choice respects tension_trajectory + tone_vector from narrative tone controller<br/>- tests use fixture beats and verify expected section envelopes selected |\\n+sdp/prd-snapshot.md:119:| CCH-039 | Embed rule-stack provenance in exported audio metadata (e.g., WAV iXML chunk or sidecar JSON) for listener-review workflow. | MUST | T1 | - each rendered audio file gets a `.render.json` sidecar with Event list, rule_stack per event, PerformanceIntent per phrase, SectionEnvelope per section, seeds, delta_track path<br/>- format documented in `my-claw/docs/render-audio-sidecar.md`<br/>- tests verify sidecar presence, schema, and ability to replay from sidecar alone |\\n+sdp/logs/Lead_T-018_20260416T054258Zb_1776371017.log:48:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"tool_result\\\",\\\"timestamp\\\":\\\"2026-04-16T20:24:39.142Z\\\",\\\"tool_id\\\":\\\"run_shell_command_1776371042532_0\\\",\\\"status\\\":\\\"success\\\",\\\"output\\\":\\\"/opt/anaconda3/lib/python3.11/site-packages/pytest_asyncio/plugin.py:252: PytestDeprecationWarning: The configuration option \\\\\\\"asyncio_default_fixture_loop_scope\\\\\\\" is unset.\\\\nThe event loop scope for asynchronous fixtures will default to the fixture caching scope. Future versions of pytest-asyncio will default the loop scope for asynchronous fixtures to function scope. Set the default fixture loop scope explicitly in order to avoid unexpected behavior in the future. Valid fixture loop scopes are: \\\\\\\"function\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"class\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"module\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"package\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"session\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\n  warnings.warn(PytestDeprecationWarning(_DEFAULT_FIXTURE_LOOP_SCOPE_UNSET))\\\\n============================= test session starts ==============================\\\\nplatform darwin -- Python 3.11.7, pytest-8.3.5, pluggy-1.5.0\\\\nsensitiveurl: .*\\\\nrootdir: /Users/anthony/Programming/PromptClaw\\\\nconfigfile: pyproject.toml\\\\nplugins: anyio-4.12.1, respx-0.22.0, cov-5.0.0, timeout-2.2.0, asyncio-1.2.0, 