itelist before touching the store, and routes through a new `create_world_entity(...)` helper that duck-types the deploy-side world store across `create_entity`/`add_entity`/`record_entity`/`upsert_entity`/`save_entity` (kwarg-shaped or single-mapping signatures). The route returns HTTP `201` with the store-assigned ID populated through the shared entity normalization pipeline so the new entity is immediately re-fetchable via `GET /world/entities/{entity_id}`, falls back to the request input for `type`/`name`/`domain`/`properties` when the store returns a partial record, and surfaces HTTP `502` when the store returns no ID, `503` when no store can be constructed, and `422` for whitelist/empty-string violations. Regression coverage in `tests/test_narrative_api_entities.py` pins the squad-member round trip via GET, each whitelisted domain, blank/missing-input rejection, downstream-failure handling, missing-store fallback, partial-record fallback, no-ID surfacing, the record-dict signature path, and shared-secret auth behavior.\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260502T001347Z_1777692683.log:+- **Details:** `PATCH /world/entities/{entity_id}` mutates the existing `properties` JSON payload on an existing entity and does not add tables, columns, or foreign keys. No migration is required.\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260502T001347Z_1777692683.log:+# Task T-015@20260502T001347Z: PATCH /world/entities/{entity_id}\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260502T001347Z_1777692683.log:+- Add `PATCH /world/entities/{entity_id}` in `app.py`:\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260502T001347Z_1777692683.log:+   through `PATCH /world/entities/{entity_id}` persists and round-trips via\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260502T001347Z_1777692683.log:+   `GET /world/entities/{entity_id}`.\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260502T001347Z_1777692683.log:+        \"/world/entities/{entity_id}\",\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260502T001347Z_1777692683.log:         \"/world/entities/{entity_id}\",\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-015_20260502T001347Z_1777692683.log