+
 - Added depth-2 federation-discovery end-to-end test coverage (frac-0071): `tests/test_federation_discovery.py` now ships a `FederationDiscoveryEndToEndTests` class that drives the existing public `discover_peers`, `save_peer_registry`, `load_peer_registry`, and `merge_peer_registry` surface end-to-end through fakes for `tailscale status --json` and the `/federation/v1/identity` endpoint. The end-to-end scenarios cover the full discover → save → load → re-scan → merge → save cycle (verifying meaningful `PeerInfo` fields, JSON-safe registry payloads, `to_dict`/`from_dict` round-trips, online/offline flag flips for vanished peers, `first_seen` preservation for returning peers, and online-on-arrival semantics for new peers), multi-IP peer fall-through where a later IP responds after an earlier IP refuses, and an empty rescan that marks every previously seen peer offline while preserving its identity and timestamps. `tests/test_test_federation_discovery_depth.py` pins `tests/test_federation_discovery.py` at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class, loading `sdp.fractal.classify_depth` via `importlib.util` to remain deterministic against the local classifier. Existing function-level federation discovery assertions and the production `promptclaw/federation/discovery.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4483 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
 
 - Added depth-2 dashboard-generator coverage and the simplest Observatory-backed class path (frac-0070): `tests/test_dashboard_generator.py` now includes `DashboardGeneratorEndToEndTests`, which builds temporary SDP, Observatory, and pet-state inputs and verifies `generate_dashboard(...)` renders meaningful service, pipeline, pet class/level, event, and timestamp output without scripts. `tests/test_test_dashboard_generator_depth.py` pins the dashboard-generator test file at fractal depth >= 2 and requires the end-to-end class. `my-claw/tools/dashboard_generator.py` now derives pet class overrides from Observatory `agent_skills` by mapping known skill categories to existing dashboard classes, accumulating score-weighted sample counts, selecting one dominant class per agent, and passing those overrides through `generate_dashboard(obs_db=...)`; missing or unreadable Observatory databases still return no class overrides. Startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4479 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green, and no new dependencies or migrations were introduced.
